This paper deals with provenance information in RDF graphs and SPARQL updates, which are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also discusses the representation of provenance information using RDF, which is related to semantic web (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of version control systems, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) research. Finally, the paper proposes a semantic framework for interpreting SPARQL updates, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) research.
